message.content: Substituting $(4, 5)$ into the equation $y = ax + b$, we find $5 = 4a + b$, or $b = 5 - 4a$. Substituting $(8, 17)$, we have $17 = 8a + b = 8a + 5 - 4a = 4a + 5$, or $a = 3/4$. Substituting this value of $a$ into $b = 5 - 4a$, we obtain $b = 5 - 4(3/4) = 5 - 3 = 2$. Therefore, $a - b = (3/4) - 2 = \boxed{-5/4}$.
